{
  "id": "ramp-task-manager",
  "kind": "problem",
  "title": "Progressive Task Manager APIs",
  "difficulty": "hard",
  "concepts": [
    "stateful design",
    "dispatch",
    "sorting",
    "intervals"
  ],
  "prompt": "Suppose an interviewer asks you to build a tiny in-memory task-management backend. The system receives a list of operations, and for each operation you return the result as a string.\n\nThink of this as a miniature API server with no database: tasks live in memory, users live in memory, and assignments have time ranges.\n\nWrite `taskManager(operations)`. Every operation is a list of strings, and the result should contain one string per operation, in the same order.\n\nTasks have an id, name, priority, and creation order. Task ids are assigned as `task_1`, `task_2`, and so on. Users have a quota: the maximum number of active assignments they can have at one time.\n\nSupported operations:\n\n- `[\"ADD\", timestamp, name, priority]`: create a task and return its new id.\n- `[\"GET\", timestamp, task_id]`: return `\"name|priority\"` for an existing task, or `\"\"` if the task does not exist.\n- `[\"UPDATE\", timestamp, task_id, new_name, new_priority]`: update an existing task. Return `\"true\"` if it existed, otherwise `\"false\"`.\n- `[\"SEARCH\", timestamp, text, limit]`: return up to `limit` task ids whose current names contain `text`. Sort by priority descending, then creation order ascending.\n- `[\"ADD_USER\", timestamp, user_id, quota]`: add a user. Return `\"false\"` if the user already exists; otherwise return `\"true\"`.\n- `[\"ASSIGN\", timestamp, task_id, user_id, finish_time]`: assign a task to a user from `timestamp` until absolute time `finish_time`. Return `\"false\"` if the task or user does not exist, if `finish_time <= timestamp`, or if the user is already at their active-assignment quota. Otherwise return `\"true\"`.\n- `[\"COMPLETE\", timestamp, task_id, user_id]`: complete that user's active unfinished assignment for the task. Return `\"true\"` if one exists, otherwise `\"false\"`.\n- `[\"USER_TASKS\", timestamp, user_id]`: return that user's active unfinished task ids at `timestamp`, sorted by task priority descending, then creation order ascending.\n- `[\"OVERDUE\", timestamp, user_id]`: return that user's unfinished task ids whose finish time is `<= timestamp`, in assignment order.\n\nAn assignment is active when `start <= timestamp < finish_time`. Completed assignments are not active and are not overdue.\n\nFor operations that return a list of ids, join the ids with commas. If the list is empty, return `\"\"`. Numeric fields such as timestamps, priorities, quotas, finish times, and limits are provided as strings.",
  "signature": {
    "name": "taskManager",
    "inputs": [
      {
        "name": "operations",
        "type": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "output": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    }
  },
  "tests": [
    {
      "name": "add and get",
      "args": [
        [
          [
            "ADD",
            "1",
            "write docs",
            "5"
          ],
          [
            "GET",
            "2",
            "task_1"
          ]
        ]
      ],
      "expected": [
        "task_1",
        "write docs|5"
      ],
      "visibility": "visible"
    },
    {
      "name": "search priority then creation order",
      "args": [
        [
          [
            "ADD",
            "1",
            "api docs",
            "3"
          ],
          [
            "ADD",
            "2",
            "api retry",
            "5"
          ],
          [
            "ADD",
            "3",
            "api auth",
            "5"
          ],
          [
            "SEARCH",
            "4",
            "api",
            "10"
          ]
        ]
      ],
      "expected": [
        "task_1",
        "task_2",
        "task_3",
        "task_2,task_3,task_1"
      ],
      "visibility": "visible"
    },
    {
      "name": "quota blocks assignment",
      "args": [
        [
          [
            "ADD_USER",
            "1",
            "u1",
            "1"
          ],
          [
            "ADD",
            "2",
            "a",
            "1"
          ],
          [
            "ADD",
            "3",
            "b",
            "1"
          ],
          [
            "ASSIGN",
            "4",
            "task_1",
            "u1",
            "10"
          ],
          [
            "ASSIGN",
            "5",
            "task_2",
            "u1",
            "12"
          ]
        ]
      ],
      "expected": [
        "true",
        "task_1",
        "task_2",
        "true",
        "false"
      ],
      "visibility": "visible"
    },
    {
      "name": "completion frees quota",
      "args": [
        [
          [
            "ADD_USER",
            "1",
            "u1",
            "1"
          ],
          [
            "ADD",
            "2",
            "a",
            "1"
          ],
          [
            "ADD",
            "3",
            "b",
            "1"
          ],
          [
            "ASSIGN",
            "4",
            "task_1",
            "u1",
            "10"
          ],
          [
            "COMPLETE",
            "6",
            "task_1",
            "u1"
          ],
          [
            "ASSIGN",
            "7",
            "task_2",
            "u1",
            "12"
          ],
          [
            "USER_TASKS",
            "8",
            "u1"
          ]
        ]
      ],
      "expected": [
        "true",
        "task_1",
        "task_2",
        "true",
        "true",
        "true",
        "task_2"
      ],
      "visibility": "hidden"
    },
    {
      "name": "overdue ignores completed",
      "args": [
        [
          [
            "ADD_USER",
            "1",
            "u1",
            "2"
          ],
          [
            "ADD",
            "2",
            "a",
            "1"
          ],
          [
            "ADD",
            "3",
            "b",
            "1"
          ],
          [
            "ASSIGN",
            "4",
            "task_1",
            "u1",
            "6"
          ],
          [
            "ASSIGN",
            "4",
            "task_2",
            "u1",
            "7"
          ],
          [
            "COMPLETE",
            "5",
            "task_1",
            "u1"
          ],
          [
            "OVERDUE",
            "8",
            "u1"
          ]
        ]
      ],
      "expected": [
        "true",
        "task_1",
        "task_2",
        "true",
        "true",
        "true",
        "task_2"
      ],
      "visibility": "hidden"
    },
    {
